**Try It Out** functionality not supported for this operation.

Clones the given submission with provided changes and optionally specified attachments.

The request body for this operation is multipart/form-data where the first part is expected to be a JSON payload
that sets most of the submission properties. Then files can be provided as additional parts, they will be
uploaded to the configured filestore and automatically associated to the appropriate value in the submission.

Example of the submission json part shown here:
```
{
  "values": {
    "fieldName": "value"
  },
  "parent": {
    "id": parentId
  },
  "origin": {
    "id": originId
  },
  "currentPage": {
    name: pageName
  },
  "coreState": "Submitted"
}
```

The additional parts (containing attachments to be uploaded) should have a field name that relates to an
attachment field on the specified form.

Example headers of an attachment part that will be associated to the *Screenshots* field
```
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="Screenshots"; filename="screenshot.png"
Content-Type: image/png
```

Building a multipart payload will differ depending on the client being used. Below is an example of building the
