```
const formData = new FormData();
formData.append("_submission", JSON.stringify(submission));
formData.append("Screenshots", fileInput.files[0], "screenshot.png")
```

## Attachment Behavior

If the values map does not specify an override for an attachment field, all of that field's attachments will be
copied when cloning the submission.

If the values map does specify an override for an attachment field, only those attachments will be copied when
cloning the submission.

Clearing all of the attachments while cloning would look like the following.

```
{
  "values": {
    "Screenshots": []
  }
}
```

Removing all but the specified attachments while cloning looks like this.

```
{
  "values": {
    "Screenshots": [
      {
        "contentType": "image/png",
        "documentId": "2022/03/23/0c1799be-aad2-11ec-8c73-31f810abd438/656dd31b-4347-4c17-9dca-5d184269e44a",
        "name": "keepme.png",
        "size": 421458
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

Finally, any files included in the multipart request will be appended to the result of the behavior described
above.

CategorizationInclude.description:
comma-separated list of properties to include in the response

* details

* category

* form

* category.{any category include property}

* form.{any form include property}
